class.description:
[CamelliaContext] implements the Camellia block cipher for use inside [CustomDecryptor] implementations. It supports Camellia-128, Camellia-192, and Camellia-256 (key length 16, 24, or 32 bytes) and exposes ECB, CBC, and CFB modes. Its API mirrors [AESContextGDRE] and [AriaContext].
Input data must be a multiple of 16 bytes; pad the buffer before passing it to [method update].
[codeblock]
func decrypt_camellia_cfb(data: PackedByteArray, key: PackedByteArray, iv: PackedByteArray) -> PackedByteArray:
    var ctx = CamelliaContext.new()
    ctx.start(CamelliaContext.MODE_CFB_DECRYPT, key, iv)
    var decrypted = ctx.update(data)
    ctx.finish()
    return decrypted
[/codeblock]
